    <h2>JAMB Correction of Data - Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>3. How much does it cost to make corrections on JAMB?</summary>
      <p>The cost is usually <strong>₦2,500</strong> per correction. Additional charges from banks or online payment platforms may apply.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>4. Can I correct my name or date of birth after writing the exam?</summary>
      <p>Yes, as long as the correction portal is still open. However, changes to sensitive information like your name or date of birth may require you to upload supporting documents such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Birth Certificate</li>
        <li>Sworn Affidavit</li>
        <li>National Identification Number (NIN) printout</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>5. How many times can I change my course or institution?</summary>
      <p>JAMB allows you to change your course or institution <strong>up to two times</strong>. Each change costs ₦2,500, and you must ensure that the new institution or course matches your qualifications.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>6. Where can I do JAMB correction of data?</summary>
      <p>You can correct your JAMB data through the following methods:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>On the JAMB official portal: <a href="https://www.jamb.gov.ng" target="_blank">https://www.jamb.gov.ng</a></li>
        <li>Through your JAMB profile</li>
        <li>At any JAMB-accredited CBT center</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>7. Is the JAMB correction of data currently ongoing?</summary>
      <p>This depends on the time of the year. The correction window usually opens shortly after the UTME results are released and remains open for a few weeks. Check the official JAMB website or social media platforms for current updates.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>8. Will changing my course or institution affect my admission chances?</summary>
      <p>It might. It’s important to choose a course or institution that aligns with your UTME score and O’Level subjects. Before making any changes, research the cut-off marks and requirements or seek guidance from a school counselor.</p>
    </details>